		<description>Caliber: 9x19mm Parabellum. 34-round detachable mag. Select-Fire.
		
A blowback-operation 9mm submachine-gun used by the British military during the Cold War. Designed by George William Patchett during WWII, the Patchett or so-called "Sterling" SMG was meant to be a replacement for the ubiquitous Sten gun. It did not end up seeing major use during the war itself, but would be adopted in the 1950s (replacing the Sten as intended), and variations of it would continue to be used in British service well into the 1990s.\nThe L2A4 variant (called the Mk.V at Sterling Armament Company), featuring an integrated spike bayonet, was tested in 1964 but never adopted.</description>
